    Interface Description

    Processes a received MV2Message.

    Class Description
    CertificateResponeMessage
    A message containing the response to a certificate request.
    ClientCertificateRequest
    A message to request the certificate allocated to a web space.
    ClientCertificateResponse
    A message containing the answer to a ClientCertificateRequest.
    ClientLoginData
    A message containing the decrypted test phrase of a ServerLoginResponse.
    ClientLoginRequest
    A message containing a client login request.
    ContentEncodingField
    A field of a message containing the encoding.
    ContentMessage
    An encrypted content message.
    DomainNamesRequest
    A message to request the available domain names from a server.
    DomainNamesResponse
    The response to a DomainNamesRequest containing the available domain names.
    EncryptedMessage
    Represents an encrypted message.
    HelloMessage
    A message to open a connection to a server.
    KeyPutRequest
    The request message to store the clients private key on the server.
    MessageDeliveryRequest
    A message containing an encrypted mail.
    MessageFetchRequest
    A message to request a mail message with the given identifier.
    MessageFetchResponse
    A message containing the response to a MessageFetchRequest.
    MessageField
    Represents a content field of a MV2Message.
    MessageParser
    A parser for parsing receiver MV2Messages.
    MessageQueryRequestMessage
    A message to request in-box messages of the current client.
    MessageQueryResponseMessage
    A message containing the identifiers of the queried mails.
    MV2CommunicationElement
    The base class for all communication elements.
    MV2Message
    A message that can be sent to a communication partner.
    ServerLoginResponse
    The servers response to a ClientLoginRequest containing the test phrase and it's digest.
    SpaceCreationRequest
    The request to create a user space.
    SpaceCreationResponse
    Represents the response message to a SpaceCreationRequest.
    UnableToProcessMessage
    Represents a message informing about the inability to process a prior message.
